<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Designer Tommy Hilfiger is selling his Greenwich estate for $47.5million just weeks after he listed his mansion in Miami for $24.5million. </p>

<p>The sprawling French Normandy-style estate was purchased by Hilfiger and his wife, 53-year-old former model Dee Ocleppo, bought the nearly 22-acre property in 2010 for $31.3million, according to the Wall Street Journal. </p>

<p>Hilfiger, who has fixed up and sold seven homes in the affluent town over the last 35 years.</p>

<p>The home is being sold at a time when New Yorkers fleeing the COVID-19 pandemic are driving up Greenwich property values.</p>

<p>Hilfiger told the Journal: 'I hear from my friends in real estate that the market is very strong, and it hasn’t been this strong in years.' </p>

<p>While he's waiting for a buyer, he and his wife are looking for a new home in Palm Beach, Florida. Hilfiger said the he and his wife have been considering the move for long time, but COVID-19 accelerated their time line. </p>

